  "answer": "Under the Massachusetts Public Records Law (M.G.L. c. 66, § 10), agencies (Records Access Officers) generally must respond to public records requests within 10 business days of receipt. This applies to requests for Medicaid (MassHealth) records as well. The initial response must either provide the records, identify the records and any applicable fees, or explain why the records cannot be provided. If more time is needed, an agency may petition the Supervisor of Records for an extension, which can extend the response time up to 20 business days for municipalities or longer with approval.",
  "source": "https://www.mass.gov/handbook/a-guide-to-the-massachusetts-public-records-law (Secretary of the Commonwealth, Public Records Division); M.G.L. c. 66, § 10",
