{
  "answer": "Under the Massachusetts Public Records Law (M.G.L. c. 66, § 10), agencies (Records Access Officers) must respond to public records requests within 10 business days of receipt. This general timeline applies to requests for records from MassHealth (the state's Medicaid program) as well. The initial response must either provide the records, identify them and give a good-faith estimate of any fees, or explain any withholdings. If more time is needed, the agency may petition the Supervisor of Records for an extension, but production generally must occur within 15 business days (for agencies) or 25 business days (for municipalities), with extensions available up to a limit.",
