  "answer": "Under the California Public Records Act (Government Code section 7922.535, formerly section 6253), agencies must determine whether a request seeks disclosable public records and notify the requester of that determination within 10 calendar days of receiving the request. In 'unusual circumstances,' this deadline may be extended by up to 14 additional calendar days with written notice to the requester. Note that this 10-day period is for the agency's determination, not necessarily the actual production of records, which should occur promptly thereafter. These rules apply to Medi-Cal (California's Medicaid program) records held by the Department of Health Care Services, subject to applicable confidentiality exemptions.",
